profile_positions.description:
Responsibilities:
-	National and international business development and acquisition;
-	Project Manager 24/7 Emergency Advisory Service to Dutch  Government on national
       disasters (floods, droughts, infrastructure, water quantity and quality);
-	Representing Deltares in national and international forums.

Syria (in missions): Programme Director Syrian-Dutch Water Cooperation (SDWC), directing a long-term programme, 2009-2015, of cooperation with the Ministry of Irrigation of Syria to implement integrated water resources management (IWRM) and water demand management practices. Project presently halted.

-	Member of several teams to prepare the formation of Deltares in 2007/8;
-	Chairman of team to formulate (concept) Marketing Plan Deltares 2007/8;
-	Advisor development of Product-Market-Teams Deltares;
-	Project Manager Emergency Advice: setting up of an advisory service in Deltares to assist the
        Ministry of Infrastructure and Environment during national calamities regarding floods, droughts
        and other emergency situations.

-	Coordinating the international cooperation activities of the organisation
-	Initiating leads, letters of interest and tender proposals for projects;
-	Coaching of staff in the formulation of proposals and the execution of projects.

-	Setting up and execution of a plan to monitor the TNO Strategic Plan 1999-2002, covering the
        14 core areas of research and 9 corporate plans;
-	Implementing a mechanism for the annual review, by the TNO Board of Management, of the
        realisation of goals and actions for each core area and each corporate development plan;
-	Communicating and liaising with the 14 TNO-institutes and staff departments at TNO
        corporate office and reporting to TNO Board of Management.

Director of Division of 150 staff. Responsible for:
-	Financial results of the division;
-	Preparing and executing the research programme;
-	Identifying new areas and topics for research and developing strategies.

Carried out the organisational development and restructuring of the unit into two separate new units. The development of a strategy and business plans for each unit and the structuring of personnel development opportunities.

Managing the department with a turnover of EUR 3.3 million. Responsible for:
-	Financial results of the department;
-	Executing cooperation projects with sister institutes in developing countries;
-	Maintaining relations with international organisations;
-	Advising national and international organisations, identifying, evaluating and formulating
        projects;
-	Supervising long-term projects abroad.

Chairman of network of four TNO institutes in the field of environmental and energy research, co-ordinating acquisition and marketing. Member of platform Geoneth, the geoscience network of Dutch research, information institutes.

Long-term technical co-operation with Kenya's Ministry of Water Development, aimed at strengthening the department’s capabil¬ities in the exploration and assessment of water resources and water resources development planning (60 staff). The WRAP project covers a number of Kenya’s arid and semi-arid areas, among which Kerio Valley, Pokot, Samburu, Isiolo, Meru Districts during the period of District Focus Policy. 
-	Advising in the planning and supervision of project activities;
-	Representing the WRAP project in meetings and other forums;
-	Member of the Inter Ministerial Steering Committee;
-	Liaising with the Kenyan competent and executing authorities;
-	Preparing the Project's Dutch budgets, responsi¬ble for expenditures;
-	Preparing progress reports and supervising the writing of techni¬cal reports;
-	Maintaining contacts with other institutions, e.g., LBDA, KVDA, Meteorolo-gical Department,
        Mines and Geology Department, University of Nairobi.

In Mozambique, March 1990: Mission to Mozambique for the revision of the Groundwater Manual "Águas Subterrâneas", 400+ pages, first completed in 1985 by undersigned.
